    "short_description": "SK hynix Inc. is a leading South Korean semiconductor company, established in 1983 and headquartered in Icheon, South Korea. Originally founded as Hyundai Electronics Industries, it became Hynix Semiconductor in 2001 and was acquired by SK Group in 2012. As the world's second-largest memory chipmaker, SK hynix specializes in advanced semiconductor memory solutions, employing around 46,255 people and generating revenues of $25,098.5 million in 2023.\n\nThe company offers a wide range of memory semiconductor products, including DDR5 DRAM, LPDDR5T mobile DRAM, and various NAND Flash storage solutions. Its products cater to diverse applications in sectors such as data centers, mobile devices, personal computers, and automotive systems. SK hynix is dedicated to innovation, particularly in AI and machine learning, and emphasizes sustainable growth through energy-efficient product development and environmental management.",
